30/05/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- All Turkish Cypriot citizens will be granted Turkish citizenship on request, according to a proposal adopted by the Turkish Parliament on Wednesday (28 May). 
The aim of the new plan is to guarantee the social and economic future of citizens of the "Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus". 
Furthermore, the Turkish government and Turkish Cypriot leadership agreed to establish a partnership council responsible for drawing up regional plans in line with joint economic and financial policies and development strategies. 
(Anadolu Agency, TRT 2, AFP - 29/05/03)
